{
  "title": "NSValue - converting scalar types to objects (in the case when a function requires an object)",
  "cells": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">An&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice x-api-no-link\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">NSValue</code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;object is a simple container for a single C or Objective-C data item. It can hold any of the scalar types such as&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">int</code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">,&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">float</code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, and&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">char</code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, as well as pointers, structures, and object&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">id</code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;references. Use this class to work with such data types in collections (such as&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice u-api\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/Cocoa/Reference/Foundation/Classes/NSArray_Class/index.html#//apple_ref/occ/cl/NSArray\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 11.8999996185303px; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 136, 204); text-decoration: none; background: transparent;\">NSArray</a></code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice u-api\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/Cocoa/Reference/Foundation/Classes/NSSet_Class/index.html#//apple_ref/occ/cl/NSSet\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 11.8999996185303px; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 136, 204); text-decoration: none; background: transparent;\">NSSet</a></code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">),&nbsp;</span><span class=\"pediaLink\" data-header=\"Key-value coding\" data-contents=\"Key-value coding is a mechanism for indirectly accessing an object’s attributes and relationships using string identifiers.\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/General/Conceptual/DevPedia-CocoaCore/KeyValueCoding.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40008195-CH25\" target=\"_self\" style=\"border: 0px; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 136, 204); text-decoration: none; background-color: transparent; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">key-value coding</a></span><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, and other APIs that require Objective-C objects.&nbsp;</span><code class=\"code-voice x-api-no-link\" style=\"border: 0px; font-size: 0.85em; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Menlo, monospace; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">NSValue</code><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;objects are always immutable.</span><div><span style=\"color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#414141\" face=\"Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal;\">NSValues are used when you need to put an non object ivar in a structure that only excepts objects&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.299999237060547px; white-space: normal;\">—</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.2999992370605px; white-space: normal;\">&nbsp;such as NSArrays, etc.</span></font></span></div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Menlo; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px; white-space: normal;\">Decode encoded c values - this converts a NSValue back into the original c struct</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "objectivec",
      "data": "[structData getValue:&info];"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Menlo; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px; white-space: normal;\">encode a c value (in this case a struct) into a objective c object that can be handles by functions that only allow objects</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "objectivec",
      "data": "NSValue *valueBackground1 = [NSValue valueWithBytes:&backgroundInfo1 objCType:@encode(GameInfo)];"
    }
  ]
}